    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Photo of Whitman, Frisking a Black Man</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Suzanne M Parson letter, commenting on July 11 article, says if Gov Chrsitne Tood Whitman is unable to understand furor over photo showing her frisking a lack man during patrol with New Jersey state troopers in 1996 she should image similar situation involving male governor and female suspect</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Gov. Christine Todd Whitman doesn't understand what was wrong with her gratuitously patting down a suspect who had already been searched by qualified law enforcement officers and was not, in fact, later charged with any crime (news article, July 11).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Gov. Christine Todd Whitman doesn't understand what was wrong with her gratuitously patting down a suspect who had already been searched by qualified law enforcement officers and was not, in fact, later charged with any crime (news article, July 11).</p>
        <p>Perhaps if she imagines a similar situation with a male governor and a female suspect, she could get a rough idea. Should we be any less upset that the victim of this confinement and groping was a black man rather than a woman?</p>
        <p>SUZANNE M. PARSON  Virgil, N.Y., July 11, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
